Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine dirty; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, perhaps two numbers Name Andronikos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum ABC 0316.31.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (31)
